Function Documentation

float cossp ( float  a  ) 

Description:
The cossp function returns the cosine of a floating-point argument a. The angle a is expressed in radians. The return value is in the range of [-1.0 and +1.0]. An argument with a large magnitude may produce a result with little or no significance.
Parameters:
[in] a = Input float
Returns:
Resultant float
Special Cases:
  • If | a | > 1.04858e+6, then the return value is zero for large angles.
See also:
  • cossp_i
  • cossp_v
Implementation Notes:
  • The code supports little endian mode.
